<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="keywords" content="BOATS, Rights of Way," /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>DDB0283</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">P Negal – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">My wife and I are regular visitors to the Yorkshire Dales  National Park and have  witnessed both  the damage that motorbikes and four-wheel drive vehicles are doing to the  Green Lanes and the  noisy  disturbance that they  create in an area that is supposed to be protected for quiet enjoyment. It is quite wrong for walkers to have  to move to one side  while  these vehicles roar past, churning up  the  surface as they  go.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We support the submissions by-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Green Lanes Environmental Action  Group (GLEAM),</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Green Lanes Protection Group (GLPG),</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The  Peak  District Green Lanes Alliance  (PDGLA) and</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Yorkshire Dales Green Lanes Alliance  (YDGLA)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">who have  proposed that -</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">1.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">All unsealed Byways Open  to All Traffic  (BOATS), and  all unsealed Unclassified County Roads (UCRs)  should be recognised as not  being part of the  ordinary roads network and  should be re­ classified as Restricted Byways.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">2. When a local authority declines to impose a traffic regulation order  that is widely supported by the public, there should be a right  of appeal, either to an  independent inspector or a magistrate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">September 2013</span></p><div style="width:auto; height:21.85pt; float:left;"><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="RAMFooter2"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">2</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">1</span></a></p></div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>